<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="1549" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1549">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/71.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Special Agent <persName type="to">Canova</persName>.</hi><note n="145" xml:id="d1549fn145">Same
                                    to Special Agent Carothers, Chihuahua.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: There is enclosed herewith, for your
                                information in connection with future representations that the
                                Department may direct you to take in regard to the situation of the
                                French priests at Zacatecas, a copy of the report from the French
                                Consular Agent at El Paso, Texas, covering the experiences of the
                                Christian Brothers of the Zacatecas School, which was transmitted to
                                the Department in a note, dated July 23d, from the French
                                Embassy.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>